01:06:49,600 --> 01:07:03,940
Thus, the Apostle says:
"Just as Jannes and Jambres opposed Moses, so these men also oppose the truth: men of corrupt minds and disapproved by God; but they will not progress further, for their folly will be plain to all, as it was with those two" (Second Timothy 3:8-9).

631
01:07:03,940 --> 01:07:09,231
It is clear that this was said about you, who could neither progress further nor conceal your folly.

632
01:07:09,231 --> 01:07:20,925
He who is baptized by the dead gains nothing (Ecclesiasticus 34:30);
indeed, he who is washed by a heretical source, and likewise he who is anointed with the oil of a sinner, that is, who is filled with an unclean spirit.

633
01:07:20,925 --> 01:07:22,883
Therefore, you will be sons of blood.

634
01:07:22,883 --> 01:07:26,322
For you do not desire the peace of the brethren, but their blood.

635
01:07:26,322 --> 01:07:27,751
Your belief is false faith.

636
01:07:27,751 --> 01:07:37,222
The adulterous woman is the heretical congregation: for the Catholic Church, from the beginning, has not left her husband's bed and chamber, nor desired foreign or strange lovers.

637
01:07:37,222 --> 01:07:49,446
You have painted an exiled form with a new color; you have separated your bed from the ancient marriage;
you have departed from the body of the one-bedded mother, adorned with new ways of pleasing and new enticements of corruption.

638
01:07:49,446 --> 01:08:09,182
For when you propose blessed Cyprian as a contrary witness to me, because in the Epistle concerning the Lapsed, he says that Moses and Daniel and Job prayed for sinners and did not obtain, as the Lord says:
"Even if these three men, Noah, Job, and Daniel, were in their midst, they would not save sons or daughters, but only they themselves would be saved" (Ezekiel 14:20).

639
01:08:09,182 --> 01:08:15,056
If only, if only you would rely on Cyprian as a witness, if only you would agree with such wholesome sentences.

640
01:08:15,743 --> 01:08:27,154
For when he urged those who had fallen to repentance, who did not want to repent, saying they had received peace from confessors or martyrs, he taught and showed that not even those patriarchs could obtain it for the unrepentant.

641
01:08:27,154 --> 01:08:29,097
Indeed, who can free someone unwilling?

642
01:08:29,097 --> 01:08:31,090
Who can humble themselves for the proud?

643
01:08:31,090 --> 01:08:32,983
Who can intercede for the unrepentant?

644
01:08:32,983 --> 01:08:36,122
When he said this, he urged them to the remedies of repentance.

645
01:08:36,122 --> 01:08:44,294
The man of such gravity and merit did not speak against himself, but he taught that prayers should be poured out by sinners and that confession should be cherished.

646
01:08:44,294 --> 01:08:51,519
Yet the examples of Cyprian move you, as he recalls that even Moses and the other saints did not obtain what they asked for on behalf of sinners.

647
01:08:51,519 --> 01:08:51,768
What?

648
01:08:51,768 --> 01:08:54,907
Don't you see that Moses couldn't obtain it for certain people?

649
01:08:54,907 --> 01:08:57,946
When he returned to the people, what did he hear in the camp?

650
01:08:57,946 --> 01:09:00,936
The voices of drunkards and the singing of idolaters echoed.

651
01:09:00,936 --> 01:09:06,616
The people were still persisting in wickedness, still remaining in the very crime, and did not know how to repent.

652
01:09:06,616 --> 01:09:09,356
But who among us told you that Moses did not obtain it?

653
01:09:09,356 --> 01:09:15,585
For God had indeed said to him, "He has sinned against me, I will blot him out of my book" (Exodus thirty-two, thirty-three).

654
01:09:15,585 --> 01:09:23,956
However, he said this with the authority of a judge and the power of the Lord; but see how quickly he reversed the sentence that was passed against the people's malice.

655
01:09:23,956 --> 01:09:24,304
Listen.

656
01:09:24,304 --> 01:09:33,074
The prophet immediately says: "And Moses prayed before the Lord his God, 'Why, Lord, do you let your anger burn against your people?' and the rest" (Exodus thirty-two, eleven).

657
01:09:33,074 --> 01:09:39,800
And further down: "And the Lord relented and did not bring on his people the disaster he had threatened" (Exodus thirty-two, fourteen).

658
01:09:39,800 --> 01:09:41,843
Do you see that God's anger was appeased?

659
01:09:41,843 --> 01:09:43,886
Do you see that the offense was placated?

660
01:09:43,886 --> 01:09:47,623
And he did not pray for the people, nor did he repent for what he had done.

661
01:09:47,623 --> 01:09:51,559
But Noah, you say, and Daniel, and Job could not save their sons and daughters.

662
01:09:51,559 --> 01:10:00,279
This is because they would ask for those who do not pray; if they intercede for those persisting in crime; if they do not defend individuals, if not a few, but many thousands.

663
01:10:00,279 --> 01:10:09,845
However, Noah saved his household from the public ruin; and Job received back all that he had lost; and Daniel, by his prayer, repelled the sword that was imminent for the wise men of Babylon.

664
01:10:10,991 --> 01:10:16,015
Certainly, for the safety of the town, Lot prays, and Paul prays for the passengers of the ship.

665
01:10:16,015 --> 01:10:19,050
Thus, those who know how to repent are freed from justice.

666
01:10:19,050 --> 01:10:22,974
Finally, I see what is written: "They alone will be saved" (Ezekiel 14:20).

667
01:10:22,974 --> 01:10:23,654
Who are they?

668
01:10:23,654 --> 01:10:28,154
They are those who intercede for sinners and plead for such people without punishment.

669
01:10:28,154 --> 01:10:29,933
And why do you condemn the Church?

670
01:10:29,933 --> 01:10:36,578
Why do you forbid interceding for those who repent, if it is also permitted to pray for those who are not allowed to obtain it?

671
01:10:36,578 --> 01:10:40,921
Therefore, read my Cyprian more diligently: read the whole letter about the Lapsed.

672
01:10:40,921 --> 01:10:45,212
Read another which he gave to Antonianus, where Novatian is urged by all examples.

673
01:10:45,212 --> 01:10:48,822
Then you will know what he pronounces about the care of the penitent.

674
01:10:48,822 --> 01:10:52,747
I speak of Cyprian, who opposes your views and upholds the Catholic rights.

675
01:10:52,747 --> 01:11:02,845
Tertullian, after his heresy for you have taken much from it you will hear in his own letter, and in that very one which he published as a Catholic, confessing that the Church can forgive sins.

676
01:11:02,845 --> 01:11:11,479
Therefore, you see that the Church is a queen in a golden and variegated garment (Psalm 45:10) composed undoubtedly of many bodies and many peoples of various kinds.

677
01:11:11,479 --> 01:11:15,769
This picture is not of one color, nor does such diversity shine in one appearance.

678
01:11:15,769 --> 01:11:18,333
One part of the garment covers, another arranges.

679
01:11:18,333 --> 01:11:23,357
Some adhere to the chest, some are drawn to the hem, and among the very edges, it becomes dirty.

680
01:11:23,357 --> 01:11:27,124
Some are compared to the purple of martyrs; others to the virginal silk.

681
01:11:27,124 --> 01:11:30,839
Some are sewn in with a folding hem, or repaired by inserting a needle.

682
01:11:30,839 --> 01:11:36,333
For one is like this, another is like that (First Corinthians 7:7); and yet one queen is composed in all.

683
01:11:36,333 --> 01:11:41,566
Therefore, the same fruitful and wealthy vine, having many branches, is extended with many clusters.

684
01:11:41,566 --> 01:11:44,129
Did none of these suffer from the cold of winter?

685
01:11:44,129 --> 01:11:45,647
Did it not endure harsh hail?

686
01:11:45,647 --> 01:11:47,688
Did it not withstand scorching summers?

687
01:11:47,688 --> 01:11:51,507
This gem is harsher on the branches, that one is stronger, another purer.

688
01:11:51,507 --> 01:11:55,118
This one spreads itself in fruits, this one overflows only in leaves.

689
01:11:55,118 --> 01:11:57,054
Yet everywhere the vine is beautiful.

690
01:11:57,054 --> 01:12:01,711
This is the mother of young women, whose number is beyond counting (Song of Solomon 6:7).

691
01:12:01,711 --> 01:12:06,891
Finally, if you can count the Catholic flocks, and reckon the swarms of our people on your fingers.

692
01:12:08,303 --> 01:12:16,532
Not only the things that are spread all over the world, filling every region, but also those things, Brother Sympronian, that are near you in the neighboring city.

693
01:12:16,532 --> 01:12:21,479
Think about how many of our people you see alone, how many of my people you encounter by yourself.

694
01:12:21,479 --> 01:12:24,255
Aren’t you like tiny drops compared to great fountains?

695
01:12:24,255 --> 01:12:26,880
Aren’t you like a drop in the ocean, being absorbed?

696
01:12:26,880 --> 01:12:31,020
Tell me, are these young women from your people, or do you alone bring them forth?

697
01:12:31,020 --> 01:12:34,250
This queen, chosen and perfected for her mother, is ours, I say.

698
01:12:34,250 --> 01:12:40,106
Nothing is chosen unless it is better and greater than something else; nothing can be perfect unless it is complete.

699
01:12:40,106 --> 01:12:48,082
Now consider this: is this particularly built upon the foundation of the prophets and apostles, with Jesus Christ himself as the cornerstone (Ephesians 2:20)?

700
01:12:48,082 --> 01:13:11,050
If it started before you, if it believed before you, if it did not leave the original foundations, if it did not move away, if it did not separate from the rest of the body, establishing its own teachers and unique instruments, if it argued anything unusual, if it discovered any new law, if it declared a rejection of peace to its own body—then it clearly seems to have departed from Christ, then it would have stood apart from the prophets and apostles.

701
01:13:11,050 --> 01:13:22,661
Therefore, this will be a great house, rich with the diversity of all kinds of vessels, where pure gold shines, and malleable silver gleams; indeed, it also honors wooden and earthen vessels as it is written (Second Timothy 2:20).

702
01:13:22,661 --> 01:13:25,790
A great house serves many purposes, requiring different works.

703
01:13:25,790 --> 01:13:29,576
It does not only seek silver, nor does it only delight in golden adornment.

704
01:13:29,576 --> 01:13:35,230
Often, a great house is more fitting with simplicity; among noble pursuits, small things can also be delightful.

705
01:13:35,230 --> 01:13:39,067
No craftsman despises his works or thinks that what he created is worthless.

706
01:13:39,067 --> 01:13:44,771
And why do you think Christ suffered for sinners, except that he did not want to lose anything he himself formed?

707
01:13:44,771 --> 01:13:57,946
Why do you think he still intercedes for the wretched today, except that he does not reject the humble and despised; he will not lose any of those he has received; even if they are compared to wood and clay, he arranges all the vessels in his house accordingly?

708
01:13:58,703 --> 01:14:01,973
Finally, brother Symproniane, don't hesitate to join the many.

709
01:14:01,973 --> 01:14:05,664
Be willing to disregard the remnants of the Novatians and your doubts.

710
01:14:05,664 --> 01:14:09,988
Consider the Catholic congregations and the people of the Church spread so widely.

711
01:14:09,988 --> 01:14:14,997
Where there is one, you will say, there I am too; and where there are two, there is the Church.

712
01:14:14,997 --> 01:14:19,321
Where there is one, let there be harmony; where there are two, let there be peace.

713
01:14:19,321 --> 01:14:23,487
Where there is one, there is the Church; how much more so where there are many?

714
01:14:23,487 --> 01:14:28,707
He says, "Two are better than one: and a threefold cord is not quickly broken" (Ecclesiastes 4:12).

715
01:14:28,707 --> 01:14:32,820
Listen to David: "I will praise your name in a great assembly" (Psalms 35:18).

716
01:14:32,820 --> 01:14:36,248
And again: "I will praise you in a mighty throng" (Psalms 35:18).

717
01:14:36,248 --> 01:14:43,050
And: "The Mighty One, God, the Lord, has spoken, and summoned the earth from the rising of the sun to its setting" (Psalms 50:1).

718
01:14:43,050 --> 01:14:48,534
What about the seed of Abraham, compared to the stars and the grains of sand, content with your poverty?

719
01:14:48,534 --> 01:14:52,225
"All the nations of the earth will be blessed in you" (Genesis 22:18).

720
01:14:52,225 --> 01:14:54,176
Tell me; does Novatian fulfill these?

721
01:14:54,176 --> 01:14:58,131
God did not redeem so little with His own blood, and Christ is not so poor.

722
01:14:58,131 --> 01:15:04,406
Recognize now, brother, the Church of God expanding its tents and fastening its tent pegs to the right and to the left.

723
01:15:04,406 --> 01:15:10,312
Understand that from the rising of the sun to its setting, the name of the Lord is to be praised (Psalms 113:3).

724
01:15:10,312 --> 01:15:16,112
See, see, I beg you, while the Novatians struggle with words, the Catholic riches are spread across the world.

725
01:15:16,112 --> 01:15:19,698
Concerning everything you consulted me about, I have instructed you.

726
01:15:19,698 --> 01:15:22,914
I have omitted nothing from the proposed topics or sentences.

727
01:15:22,914 --> 01:15:25,340
I have responded to the very points and words.

728
01:15:25,340 --> 01:15:32,037
If you sought with a consulting spirit, it has been shown lovingly: if with a challenging spirit, it has been debated promptly.

729
01:15:32,037 --> 01:15:37,257
I will append another letter when there is time, in which I will not refute yours but present ours.

730
01:15:37,257 --> 01:15:40,685
If you read kindly and without disdain, perhaps it will not harm.

731
01:15:40,685 --> 01:15:44,007
Meanwhile, in this, I ask that you review each thing carefully.

732
01:15:44,007 --> 01:15:46,485
Everything quickly read is quickly passed over.

733
01:15:46,485 --> 01:15:51,811
If you desire better gifts and bear a soul of good learning, you will not easily disdain such truths.

734
01:15:51,811 --> 01:15:57,400
May the Lord deign to keep and protect you forever, and make you live as a Christian in spiritual harmony.

735
01:15:57,400 --> 01:15:57,664
Amen.

